---
// src/pages/projects/project-2.astro
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Obscuratee™" backgroundColor="#0f0f0d">
  <main class="project-detail-container">
    <article class="project-detail" transition:name="project-2">
      <a href="/projects" class="back-link">
        <span class="arrow">←</span>
        <span>back to projects</span>
      </a>
      <div class="project-header">
        <h1>Obscuratee™</h1>
        <span class="tag">Python</span>
      </div>

      <p class="project-intro">
        A whimsical terminal application that brings colorful ASCII manatees to
        your command line, delivering marine-inspired wisdom with questionable
        accuracy. Because sometimes your terminal needs more manatees.
      </p>

      <div class="project-content">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
          At the intersection of marine biology and questionable priorities,
          Obscuratee emerges as the premier platform for delivering factually
          ambiguous aquatic knowledge directly to your terminal. It's like if
          cowsay and pokemon-colorscripts had a child... just worse... and with
          a manatee. Featuring multiple display modes including legacy ASCII
          art, vibrant color modes, and special curse effects that make your
          terminal truly shine.
        </p>

        <h2>Key Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Full color ASCII manatees with vibrant terminal output</li>
          <li>
            Multiple display modes: default color, legacy ASCII, and vibe mode
          </li>
          <li>Curse mode for terminal glow-up with special effects</li>
          <li>Marine-inspired factoids with questionable accuracy</li>
          <li>Simple pip installation and command-line interface</li>
          <li>Published on PyPI for easy distribution</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Challenges & Solutions</h2>
        <p>
          One of the main challenges was designing ASCII art that looks good
          both in legacy monochrome and modern color modes while maintaining
          terminal compatibility across different systems. The solution involved
          creating modular display modes with fallback options and ANSI color
          support for enhanced visual appeal without breaking older terminal
          emulators.
        </p>

        <div class="project-links">
          <a
            href="https://pypi.org/project/obscuratee/"
            class="project-link-btn primary"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            <span>PyPI Package</span>
            <span class="arrow">→</span>
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/snezzz0/obscuratee"
            class="project-link-btn"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            <span>View Code</span>
            <span class="arrow">→</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .project-detail-container {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 4rem 2rem 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .back-link {
    position: absolute;
    top: -3rem;
    left: 0;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    color: #c5c9c5;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-family: "Fira Code", "FiraCode Nerd Font", monospace;
    transition: color 0.2s;
    z-index: 10;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: #9c8d7e;
  }

  .arrow {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .project-detail {
    background: #1d1c19;
    border: 3px solid #c5c9c5;
    padding: 2.5rem 2rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    width: 100%;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .project-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .project-header h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: #c5c9c5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .tag {
    background: #9c8d7e;
    color: #0f0f0d;
    padding: 0.4rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    border: 1px solid #9c8d7e;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .project-intro {
    color: #9c8d7e;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .project-content h2 {
    color: #c5c9c5;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .project-content p {
    color: #9c8d7e;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .project-content ul {
    color: #727169;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .project-link-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    color: #9c8d7e;
    border: 2px solid #9c8d7e;
    padding: 1rem 1.75rem;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    font-family: "Fira Code", "FiraCode Nerd Font", monospace;
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .project-link-btn.primary {
    background: #9c8d7e;
    color: #0f0f0d;
  }

  .project-link-btn:hover {
    background: #9c8d7e;
    color: #0f0f0d;
  }

  .project-link-btn.primary:hover {
    background: #9c8d7e;
    border-color: #9c8d7e;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .project-detail-container {
      padding: 3rem 1rem 2rem;
    }

    .back-link {
      top: -2.5rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .project-detail {
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }

    .project-header {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }

    .project-header h1 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .project-links {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .project-link-btn {
      width: 100%;
      justify-content: center;
    }
  }
</style>
